The study was to be published in Wednesday's Journal of the American Medical Association, along with other studies on obesity.
A study released by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention showed that the number of Americans considered obese --defined as being more than 30 percent over their ideal body weight -- soared from about one in eight in 1991 to nearly one in five last year.
